Author:  MORRiS
Vol / Page:  227
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Kainga,</i> and <i>Kaika, n. </i> now generally <i>kaik</i>, and pronounced<i> kike</i>, a Maori settlement, village. <i>Kainga</i> is used in the North, and is the original form; <i>Kaika</i> is the South island use. it is the village for dwelling; the <i>pa</i> is for fighting in.
